<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF1FFAFFF4CFC373F54FBC6" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF1FFAFFF4CFC373F54FBC6" blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFF4CFC373F0AFC52" bold="true" box="[199,334,988,1014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named for Howard Everest Hinton (1912–1977) one of the coleopterists of the twentieth century, who was born and raised in 
<collectingCountry id="F3707615FFF1FFAFFD3CFBEB3D4BFBBE" box="[695,783,1024,1050]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and collected the unique 
<typeStatus id="54DC8827FFF1FFAFFBCAFBEB3AE3FBBE" box="[1089,1191,1024,1050]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">holotype</typeStatus>
. In a coincidence, he started his university education at the same institution as one of us (MAI), Modesto Junior College in Modesto, California.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF1FFAFFF4CFB873C30FA9F" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF1FFAFFF4CFB873C30FA9F" blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFF4CFB873F06FB22" bold="true" box="[199,322,1132,1158]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFEC7FB873C5FFB22" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[332,539,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hintoni">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFEC7FB873C5FFB22" box="[332,539,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Chespirito hintoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFCFEFB873DAFFB22" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller and Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[885,1003,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFCFEFB873DAFFB22" box="[885,1003,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Chespirito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of a unicolorous brownish pronotum and elytra (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFE7BFB7B3C01FB0E" box="[496,581,1168,1194]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) (vs. the yellow pronotal disc in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFC23FB7B3A0FFB0E" box="[936,1099,1168,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ballantynae">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFC23FB7B3DFFFB0E" box="[936,955,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFC4CFB7B3A0FFB0E" box="[967,1099,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">ballantynae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the pronotum not constricted medially (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFE82FB5F3F24FB6A" box="[265,352,1204,1230]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) (vs. constricted in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFDC8FB5F3C96FB6A" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[579,722,1204,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFDC8FB5F3C12FB6A" box="[579,598,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFDEFFB5E3C96FB6A" box="[612,722,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the last three abdominal segments distinctly yellow (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFAB5FB5F3EFFFB56" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1D, 1G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFF41FB333EAAFB56" box="[202,238,1240,1266]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lateral habitus of Chespirito species. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Apically notched and bifurcated ventrite 7 in detail. D–E) C. milleri. Scale bars: A–C = 1 mm, D–E = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405136/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">2A</figureCitation>
) (vs. dark brown in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFE57FB333C7BFB56" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[476,575,1240,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lloydi">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFE57FB333FABFB56" box="[476,495,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFE74FB333C7BFB56" box="[511,575,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">lloydi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or not distinctly yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFCF6FB333A4AFB56" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[893,1038,1240,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFCF6FB333DD4FB56" box="[893,912,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFC2BFB323A4AFB56" box="[928,1038,1241,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by having ventrite 8 notched medially (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFE83FB173F19FAB2" box="[264,349,1276,1302]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
) (vs. entire in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFE75FB173C24FAB2" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[510,608,1276,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lloydi">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFE75FB173C55FAB2" box="[510,529,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFD95FB173C24FAB2" box="[542,608,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">lloydi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFDEAFB173C92FAB2" box="[609,726,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFDE0FB173C92FAB2" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[619,726,1276,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">C. milleri</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFC80FB173D37FAB2" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[779,883,1276,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costae">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFC80FB173D5AFAB2" box="[779,798,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFCA0FB163D37FAB2" box="[811,883,1277,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">costae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and tergite 8 entire, round apically (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFA85FB173B27FAB2" box="[1294,1379,1276,1302]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
) (vs. tergite VIII notched apically in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF1FFAFFE73FACB3C20FA9E" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[504,612,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFE73FACB3C20FA9E" box="[504,612,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C. milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF1FFAFFF4CFAAF3B77F94F" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF1FFAFFF4CFAAF3C49F962" blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFF4CFAAF3F1DFAFA" bold="true" box="[199,345,1348,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Description.</emphasis>
General color dark brown (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFD05FAAF3CB6FAFA" box="[654,754,1348,1374]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1A</figureCitation>
); mandibles and last three abdominal segments yellow (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFAEFFAAF3EFFFA26" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFF43FA833EAAFA26" box="[200,238,1384,1410]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lateral habitus of Chespirito species. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Apically notched and bifurcated ventrite 7 in detail. D–E) C. milleri. Scale bars: A–C = 1 mm, D–E = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405136/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">2A</figureCitation>
); tarsi and metaventrite slightly lighter than remaining ventrites of the body. Head as long as wide, nearly covered by pronotum, only anterior 1/4 visible (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFD4BFA673D5FFA02" box="[704,795,1420,1446]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Antenna short and stubby, when extending posteriorly barely surpassing humeral region (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFDAEFA5B3CC4FA6E" box="[549,640,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum not constricted medially; anterior angles round; posterior margin bisinuate (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFEEDFA3F3F86FA4A" box="[358,450,1492,1518]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); with median longitudinal carina strongly visible throughout (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFB1EFA3F3AB4FA4A" box="[1173,1264,1492,1518]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Elytra ca. 4× length of pronotum; moderately dehiscent; basally subparallel (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFCD6FA133DF2F9B6" box="[861,950,1528,1554]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); with two weakly developed elytral costae (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFF2BF9F73EB3F992" box="[160,247,1564,1590]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Scutellar shield round posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFD01F9F73CA6F992" box="[650,738,1564,1590]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Tergite VIII entire, apically round (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFBF3F9F73A8BF992" box="[1144,1231,1564,1590]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of abdominal ventrite 7 with a deep V-shaped notch (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFC8EF9AB3D24F9FE" box="[773,864,1600,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
); ventrite 8 elongate, fusiform, longer than wide, medially notched apically (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFE42F98F3C67F9DA" box="[457,547,1636,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia with median lobe stout, slightly fusiform, apically rounded, in ventral view bearing paired strut-like structure (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFD31F9633D52F906" box="[698,790,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); parameres apically rounded (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF1FFAFFBFCF9633A97F906" box="[1143,1235,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
), 1/5 shorter than median lobe; phallobase missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF1FFAFFF4CF93B3B77F94F" blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" box="[199,1331,1744,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFF4CF93B3D7EF94E" bold="true" box="[199,826,1744,1770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Length (exposed portion of head+pronotum+elytra):</emphasis>
<quantity id="4C9F9B60FFF1FFAFFCCAF93B3DDEF94F" box="[833,922,1744,1771]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF1FFAFFC2EF93B3A8AF94E" bold="true" box="[933,1230,1744,1770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Width (across humerus):</emphasis>
<quantity id="4C9F9B60FFF1FFAFFB5DF93B3B6BF94F" box="[1238,1327,1744,1771]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF1FFAFFF4CF91F3CF9F8AA" box="[199,701,1780,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF1FFAFFF4CF91F3CF9F8AA" blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" box="[199,701,1780,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
